title: Over Protocol: Superblock Raises $8 Million for New Layer 1 Blockchain Focusing on Lightweight Full Nodes - ZyCrypto
content:
Advertisement

Superblock, a contributor to Over Protocol, has raised $8M in two fundraising rounds from well-known businesses and VCs in South Korea. SK, Netmarble, DSC, E&Investment, Schmidt, SpringCamp, and NaverZ were among the investors.

“We are deeply diving into the South Korea market with the best local partners and looking to meet global partners, accelerating us all over the world.” – Ben (Jae-Yun) Kim, the founder of Superblock.

The expenses of bootstrapping and maintaining nodes have increased over time as layer 1 blockchains have grown quicker and more established. As a result, operating blockchain applications without the usage of expensive technology has become difficult.

A new layer 1 blockchain called Over Protocol is based on the “Ethanos” protocol, which only accepts active accounts as genuine. This allows full nodes to reject old data and use less storage, which lowers the amount of storage needed. Anyone will be able to run a node and function as a validator using Over on their home PCs. At EuroSys’21, Ethanos has been published.

“With the ability for anyone to run a validator, individuals can earn $over through a process called home staking, enabling them to embrace a new lifestyle with new payment options, enhanced credit, and innovative finance opportunities,” Ben added.

title: Crypto Trader Warns It Could Get ‘Really Ugly’ for Binance Coin (BNB), Updates Outlook on Two Ethereum Rivals - The Daily Hodl
content:
A widely followed crypto trader is issuing a warning on Binance Coin (BNB) as he charts the path forward for two Ethereum (ETH) competitors.

Pseudonymous trader Altcoin Sherpa tells his 195,900 Twitter followers that BNB, the utility token of the Binance Smart Chain, is flashing ominous signs.

According to Altcoin Sherpa, BNB could plunge by over 20% to revisit lows last reached in June of 2022 if the current support level fails to hold.

“BNB: It gets really ugly below these lows. $180-ish or lower is the area you’d view if this current region gets lost. Lots of Fear, Uncertainty and Doubt (FUD) around this one, I wouldn’t personally long here.”

BNB is trading at $244 at time of writing.

Next up is Avalanche (AVAX). While predicting that the Ethereum rival could appreciate over the medium term, the pseudonymous crypto analyst urges caution as Avalanche hovers below the 200-period exponential moving average (EMA).

“AVAX: 200 day EMA right here so be careful. But I think this goes higher in the midterm.”

Avalanche is trading at $14.28 at time of writing.

Turning to Cosmos (ATOM), Altcoin Sherpa says that the 26th-largest crypto asset by market cap is facing dim prospects over the short to medium term.

“ATOM: I don’t really see this being a great one in the short or mid-term. The fundamentals are good but I just don’t see a reason to buy this as of right now. ATOM did excellent in 2021 but I think it is going to continue to consolidate for a while.”

Cosmos is trading at $9.52 at time of writing.

title: China Says BTC, BNB Are Top Crypto Coins, QUBE Next? | Bitcoinist.com - Bitcoinist
content:
As the crypto sector continues to mature, fresh dynamics and emerging trends continually reshape the market outlook. One recent notable development is the apparent shift in China’s stance towards cryptocurrencies. Known for its rigid regulatory position, China has been predominantly critical of the digital asset class. However, recent developments suggest a possible reversal in its outlook. While Bitcoin (BTC) and Binance Coin (BNB) have been singled out as top performers, whispers have started to circulate about the potential addition of InQubeta (QUBE) to this elite list.

Bitcoin (BTC) and Binance Coin (BNB)

Bitcoin, the first and most influential cryptocurrency, has undeniably captured the attention of many, including China. Despite regulatory scrutiny, it appears that the undeniable influence of BTC on the global financial landscape may be causing a shift in the country’s attitude. The fact that Bitcoin has remained resilient amidst the global economic turmoil and continues to command a large market share makes it hard to ignore.

Similarly, Binance Coin (BNB), the native token of the world’s largest cryptocurrency exchange Binance, has also caught China’s attention. BNB’s impressive performance is attributable to Binance’s consistent growth and innovation, cementing its place as one of the top crypto coins.

InQubeta (QUBE) – The Emerging Contender

InQubeta (QUBE), an innovative blockchain project enabling fractional investment in AI startups, is also making waves in the crypto space. The project’s unique proposition, combined with its promising tokenomics, has stirred interest among diverse investors. While QUBE is not currently on China’s radar as a top crypto coin, the innovative functionalities and value proposition it brings to the table might soon alter this.

InQubeta’s mission is to democratize AI investment, a goal that has garnered the attention of many in the crypto industry. The platform’s robust utility token, QUBE, is more than just a speculative asset. It’s a gateway to the exciting world of AI start-ups and plays a crucial role in the platform’s unique fractional investment system.

The Future for QUBE?

With InQubeta’s potential for creating a paradigm shift in the AI investment landscape, it is reasonable to speculate whether QUBE might be the next crypto coin to catch China’s attention. The project’s unique value proposition and robust tokenomics make it a strong contender.

However, despite the whispers, it’s crucial to understand that the journey to recognition by China, or any other major economic power, isn’t straightforward. While Bitcoin and Binance Coin have made their marks, they’ve also been subjected to extensive scrutiny and regulatory hurdles. The same might be expected for InQubeta if it comes under China’s watchful eye.

That said, if InQubeta continues to execute its vision successfully, proving its utility and carving out a niche in the blockchain and AI space, it’s plausible that the project might gain greater recognition.

The Bottom Line

While China’s official recognition of BTC and BNB as top cryptos is a significant milestone for these digital assets, it is not the only benchmark for success. Many other promising projects like InQubeta are shaping the future of the industry. It will be interesting to see if QUBE joins the ranks of BTC and BNB in China’s perspective. However, regardless of what the future holds, the intrinsic value and utility of InQubeta (QUBE) will continue to make it an exciting prospect for investors globally.
